            <paragraph><strong>Note:</strong> Synchronization is not supported for <reference internal="True" refuri="class_object#class-object"><inline classes="std std-ref">Object</inline></reference> type properties, like <reference internal="True" refuri="class_resource#class-resource"><inline classes="std std-ref">Resource</inline></reference>. Properties that are unique to each peer, like the instance IDs of <reference internal="True" refuri="class_object#class-object"><inline classes="std std-ref">Object</inline></reference>s (see <reference internal="True" refuri="class_object#class-object-method-get-instance-id"><inline classes="std std-ref">Object.get_instance_id()</inline></reference>) or <reference internal="True" refuri="class_rid#class-rid"><inline classes="std std-ref">RID</inline></reference>s, will also not work in synchronization.</paragraph>
